WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.120 --> 00:00:06.130
Dr. Bowden: My name is Dr. Jonny Bowden.

00:00:06.130 --> 00:00:07.450
I'm a board-certified nutritionist.

00:00:07.450 --> 00:00:09.469
I also have a master's degree in psychology.

00:00:09.469 --> 00:00:13.559
I've written 14 books, and my passion is helping
people feel good about themselves and having

00:00:13.559 --> 00:00:14.760
a great life.

00:00:14.760 --> 00:00:20.680
Unleash Your Thin is our first diet program
ever in 14 books of writing about diets and

00:00:20.680 --> 00:00:25.529
telling people how to make sense of diet programs
and what makes sense and what doesn't and

00:00:25.529 --> 00:00:27.369
what's a myth and what isn't.

00:00:27.369 --> 00:00:31.850
It's the first time that I've actually put
a program together with my own name on it.

00:00:31.850 --> 00:00:35.610
What it does that's a little bit different
than any other diet program I've ever done

00:00:35.610 --> 00:00:42.129
or that I've ever seen is that it looks at
an aspect of weight loss that tends to get

00:00:42.129 --> 00:00:44.852
neglected in a lot of the other programs.

00:00:44.852 --> 00:00:50.280
See, people don't do what they're supposed
to do, not because they don't have the information.

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:54.230
I have never met a person in my life who was
smoking cigarettes because they didn't get

00:00:54.230 --> 00:00:55.589
the memo about lung cancer.

00:00:55.589 --> 00:01:00.250
I've never met someone and said to them, "Do
you know those things cause cancer?" and they

00:01:00.250 --> 00:01:01.250
go, "My God.

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:03.800
Nobody ever told me," and they take their
Marlboros and throw them out.

00:01:03.800 --> 00:01:06.490
So clearly, there's another aspect to this.

00:01:06.490 --> 00:01:11.430
Most people know what they need to do to accomplish
anything, whether it's stopping smoking, losing

00:01:11.430 --> 00:01:14.830
weight, getting healthy, going to college,
getting a divorce.

00:01:14.830 --> 00:01:16.860
They know what the steps are.

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:21.850
What stops them is some belief that they can't
accomplish this.

00:01:21.850 --> 00:01:26.420
Some other thing gets in the way, and what
Unleash Your Thin does, it spends at least

00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:29.640
one-third of the time talking about that other
thing.

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:34.440
What stops you from doing what you know would
really work for you and get you where you

00:01:34.440 --> 00:01:35.440
want to go?

00:01:35.440 --> 00:01:38.850
In the case of food, it has a lot to do with
addiction.

00:01:38.850 --> 00:01:40.070
We're addicted to food.

00:01:40.070 --> 00:01:43.850
We're addicted to the foods that make us that
tired, sick, and depressed.

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:46.840
These foods have been engineered in very clever
ways.

00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:52.310
Scientists actually overlay these foods with
precise layers of the types of things, like

00:01:52.310 --> 00:01:56.950
salt, fat, and sugar, that literally light
up our brain chemistry and get our dopamine

00:01:56.950 --> 00:02:01.590
neurons firing so that we feel craving and
we feel we have to have these foods.

00:02:01.590 --> 00:02:03.780
Will power really only goes so far with that.

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:07.680
Will power is kind of ... It'll get you so
far, but it's kind of like holding onto a

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:08.800
ledge with your fingernails.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:10.900
Eventually, you're going to let go.

00:02:10.900 --> 00:02:15.040
What we do in Unleash Your Thin is we talk
about why these foods have the kind of hold

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:19.599
they have over us, why when you walk into
a food court and you smell a Cinnabon, you

00:02:19.599 --> 00:02:20.599
must have it.

00:02:20.599 --> 00:02:23.999
You cannot say no to it, or it's very hard
to say no to it.

00:02:23.999 --> 00:02:28.349
We work on those kinds of associations that
we have to food that make them addictive.

00:02:28.349 --> 00:02:33.670
We try to break that down and actually reprogram
our brain so that we are not the victim of

00:02:33.670 --> 00:02:39.249
these cravings, but instead, have some mastery
over them.

00:02:39.249 --> 00:02:43.450
Everybody has different trigger foods, so
rather than just give a list of these are

00:02:43.450 --> 00:02:49.180
the foods you should never eat, which, by
the way, we do, but for most people there

00:02:49.180 --> 00:02:51.680
are certain foods that are like their triggers
foods.

00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:53.290
You just can't say no to these.

00:02:53.290 --> 00:02:57.209
These are the ones that are just going to
derail you no matter what.

00:02:57.209 --> 00:03:01.129
We do a lot of individual work in Unleash
Your Thin where people actually identify what

00:03:01.129 --> 00:03:02.829
those foods are for them.

00:03:02.829 --> 00:03:04.760
What are the foods they can't say no to?

00:03:04.760 --> 00:03:08.849
We talk a lot about things like wheat and
grains, which are bad for a lot of people,

00:03:08.849 --> 00:03:10.319
but not for everybody.

00:03:10.319 --> 00:03:15.969
We're not big believers in the one-size-fits-all
theory on any aspect of diet.

00:03:15.969 --> 00:03:20.379
What we try to do in Unleash Your Thin is
actually have people, through journaling and

00:03:20.379 --> 00:03:25.540
through keeping notes on how they're affected
by different foods, discover which foods are

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:28.690
really the ones that are derailing their whole
program.

00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:30.400
Then they can take those foods out.

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:35.480
If those foods really are not problems for
them, then we have a template, an infrastructure,

00:03:35.480 --> 00:03:38.930
